post_text:
ANNOUNCEMENT:

Effective Thursday March 26th, Golden Door Charter School will be providing a "grab-n-go" lunch every Monday through Thursday from 11am-12pm outside of the Administrative Building (3040 Kennedy Blvd) for students who qualify for free or reduced lunch. Every Thursday, parents will have the option to obtain lunches for both Thursday and Friday. Parents are asked to ring the bell of the Administrative Building and wait outside in the courtyard at a safe distance while the bagged lunch is delivered to you. Our food service provider will wear gloves and all other precautions will be taken for the safety of parents and staff. If you plan to pick up food during the week, we are requesting that you contact Ms. Gomes in the main office at 201-795-4400 (Opt 0) to let her know so we can better gage how much to order and not waste food during these trying times. Thank you.
